The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Universal Cables inks pact
                                                                                                               Universal Cables inks pact
                            
	Calcutta, April 24 (PTI): MP Birla group company Universal Cables has entered into a joint venture agreement with Japan-based Furukawa Electric Company to manufacture and market optical fibres.        
	A spokesperson for Universal Cables said the strategic alliance would combine the companys strong understanding of the Indian market with Furukawas presence in the international markets.        
	According to the agreement, Universal Cables would hold 55 per cent in the joint entity.         
	The chairman of the joint venture board will be nominated from Universals nominee directors.                                                                                                                                       
